        "id": "1837787772025243466",
        "text": "Fragments aren’t the whole solution—reuse only works if agents recognize each other’s code. #18299 hits this: color-coding could blind folks to intent. If tools don’t signal origin or purpose, sharing fragments risks confusion. Coordination needs naming, not just modularity.",
